Okay, so there's a slight problem.

The output log is too big to actually be able to upload it on a site. Most of it is NullReferenceExceptions.

A quote while I try and figure this mess out.

"(Filename: C:/buildslave/unity/build/artifacts/StandalonePlayerGenerated/UnityEngineDebug.cpp Line: 56)

PartCompiler: Cannot clone model 'VenStockRevamp/Squad/Parts/Command/CommandPods/MK2LanderCan' as model does not exist"

I assume youre using the latest version of MM? v2.6.11 IIRC... Also, dig through all the mod folders in Gamedata, and remove any duplicate/older versions of MM...Sometimes having multiple copies of MM in the Gamedata folder can cause issues...You can try having just one copy of the latest version, in the main Gamedata folder, not in a sub-folder... I know Ven's Revamp includes an older copy of MM, as do many other mods...Try deleting that...

Have you pruned your stock parts at all?...Do you use Active Texture Management?....

You can also scan thru the KSP.log in the main install folder, and look for [ERR] & [WRN] for clues, if you havent already...I find THIS log more helpful when weird stuff happens during game loading, or during gameplay, with NO crashing...I believe the output.log is more for when the game completely crashes, or has extreme issues during gameplay...???

EDIT: Ooops...Sorry, latest STABLE vers. of MM is 2.6.8... 2.6.11 is a dev version I've been using... Also, I think you can try deleting the ModuleManager.ConfigCache, MM.ConfigSHA, MM.Physics, & MM.TechTree files in the main Gamedata folder...
